<div id="content" lang="en" dir="ltr">
When Groo speaks, he says <p>
"Groo, the wanderer 1" 
</p>
<p>
If I recall correctly he has nothing to say until afraid, so he says '1' which is buggy. 
</p>
<p>
The code should handle one-character unique speak as "don't say anything". 
</p>
<p>
<a href="./MassimilianoMarangio">MassimilianoMarangio</a>: I've added some lines to fix the problem. Next step is to modify the function get_xtra_line in files.c such that 0 lines are allowed. 
</p>
